  "parent": "cel",
  "notes": "Celtiberian (3rd–1st c. BCE). Continental Celtic language of the upper Ebro valley and Meseta. Attested in ~200 inscriptions in Iberian semi-syllabary and Latin alphabet. Key feature: Celtic p-loss (no native /p/). Preserves *-nd- cluster. Intervocalic lenition of stops (pan-Celtic). Five-vowel system with phonemic length. Two sibilants debated. Classification: Celtic > Continental > Hispano-Celtic.",
